The Rodrigues Centre shall –
* act as the main institution in Rodrigues for coordinating and monitoring the implementation of disaster risk reduction and management activities as per the Rodrigues Strategic Framework and Plan;
* coordinate and monitor the implementation of the disaster risk reduction and management programmes through community participation and public awareness campaigns;
* work in close collaboration with the Mauritius Meteorological Services, which shall develop and improve warnings and advisories systems for all natural hazards affecting Rodrigues;
* implement a multi-hazard emergency alert system with the support of the National Centre which will provide accurate and timely advice to the public and key stakeholders;
* support Commissions, departments and communities in building capacity for disaster risk reduction and management;
* facilitate and coordinate the conduct of regular trainings, drills and simulation exercises to test the adequacy of disaster response plans;
* undertake and participate in post-disaster reviews, including lessons drawn from previous disasters in disaster preparedness and response plans;
* assist relevant stakeholders to develop an appropriate risk transfer mechanism for post-disaster recovery and rehabilitation purposes;
* collaborate with all relevant stakeholders so that disaster risk reduction and management becomes an integral objective of environment-related policies and plans, sound land use planning, natural resources management, education and social development plans, economic and sectoral policies, as well as infrastructure through enforcement of building codes;
* foster cooperation in disaster risk reduction management issues, including best practices and sharing of expertise; and
* every 6 months, submit a periodical report related to its activities to the Rodrigues Council.

